# AlphaNonNull.Core.Inert

**Paper 68: Inert — not actively grounding, structuring, or underwriting.**

Inert(α) means α is a passive backdrop: not actively grounding, structuring,
or underwriting articulation/manifestation. Distinct from Null (sheer absence)
and SemanticallySterile (incapable of underwriting). Blocks the "passive
backdrop" attack: Alpha is not nothing, not sterile, and not inert.

Defined independently of Null and SemanticallySterile.
-/

